data.title: RM of Prairie Rose #309 – Saskatchewan Canada
data.text:
The Village of Jansen is a small community located in the heart of mid-Saskatchewan, just off Yellowhead Highway 16. Surrounding by soil rich in potash, the community is a short distance from the Nutrien Lanigan Potash Mine and the BHP Canada Inc Jansen Mine Site.

Thank You to the Saskatchewan Gov’t for Funding the New Radar Signs!

Helping To Make Our Community Safer!!!
